<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - WATER PUMP AND THERMOSTAT - WATER PUMP AND THERMOSTAT</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>WATER PUMP AND THERMOSTAT</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the two bolts and lock washers from the coolant outlet elbow,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350703">7.3</hotlnk>,
                    </emph>
                    1988 model year and earlier shown.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the coolant outlet elbow, gasket and thermostat from the crankcase. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350704">7.4</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Discard the gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the two coolant inlet bolts and washers, as shown in
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350705">7.5</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Remove the inlet housing and gasket. Discard the gasket.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4350703" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12376" filename="../figcg1/CG12376.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.3</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350704" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12377" filename="../figcg1/CG12377.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.4</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350705" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12378" filename="../figcg1/CG12378.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.5</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">While preventing pulley movement with a pry bar, loosen and remove the 4 pulley
                    retaining bolts, then remove the pulley from the water pump hub. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_138.xml" xrefid="ef4350706">7.6</hotlnk>,
                    </emph>
                    1988 model year and earlier shown.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 14 bolts and washers which secure the water pump to the front plate and
                    crankcase. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_138.xml" xrefid="ef4350707">7.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Note the location of the different bolt lengths. Remove the gasket and discard.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
